The Biden-Harris Administration has made racial equity a priority and has taken several actions to address systemic racism and promote economic opportunity for African American communities. They have implemented policies that have led to record drops in unemployment for Black workers, low credit card delinquency rates, low foreclosures and evictions, and low child poverty rates. The administration has also focused on lowering healthcare costs and improving access to healthcare for Black communities, promoting mental health for Black youth, ensuring equitable educational opportunities, appointing a historic number of Black women to the bench, launching initiatives to advance equity and justice for underserved communities, advancing diversity and inclusion in the federal workforce, and working towards equal justice in the criminal justice system. Additionally, the administration is committed to advancing public safety in Black communities and protecting voting rights and democracy. They are also dedicated to reforming the immigration system and providing legal protections for Black noncitizens.